# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Type: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore, perf
# Scope: ui, wizard, backend, build, theme, docs, wifi, moonraker
#
# Subject: Imperative mood, lowercase, no period (50 chars max)
# Example: "add printer identification screen"
#
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Body: Explain WHAT and WHY (not HOW). Wrap at 72 characters.
# - Use bullet points for multiple changes
# - Reference issues/tickets: Refs #123
# - Explain motivation and context
#
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Footer: Breaking changes, issue references
# BREAKING CHANGE: (if applicable, explain what breaks)
# Closes #123
# Refs #456
#
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Examples:
#
# feat(wizard): add printer identification screen
#
# Implements step 3 of the wizard flow allowing users to name their
# printer. Uses text input with validation for non-empty names.
#
# Refs #234
#
# ────────────────────────
#
# fix(wifi): resolve thread blocking UI updates
#
# Changed connect_thread_.join() to detach() to prevent blocking the
# LVGL main thread during WiFi connection attempts. This was causing
# button state updates to be delayed by 2-3 seconds.
#
# Button states now update immediately on click as expected.
#
# Refs #156
#
# ────────────────────────
#
# docs(architecture): compress CLAUDE.md using table format
#
# Reduced from 809 to 211 lines (74% reduction) by:
# - Converting Critical Rules to table (100→5 lines)
# - Converting Critical Patterns to table (160→12 lines)
# - Condensing Architecture section with link to ARCHITECTURE.md
# - Adding lazy-load instructions for large docs
#
# Estimated token savings: ~4,100 tokens per session startup
#
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Commit Template Usage:
# 1. Enable: git config commit.template .gitmessage
# 2. Commit: git commit (editor opens with this template)
# 3. Fill in <type>, <scope>, <subject>, and body
# 4. Delete comments (lines starting with #)
# 5. Save and close editor
#
# Reference: CONTRIBUTING.md "Git Commit Standards"
